			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">The story of my bard...(partial guide 1-39)<a name="31934"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 31 04 10:42 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>First I had a bard on the same account as my 65 shaman and it didnt get played because I was a newbie that didnt know how to play a bard.  So on my 2nd account I made a bard I could power level, which I did in Field of bone till lv 10.  After reading guides here I found you can do the pit AE style for fast leveling.
<br />

<br />
I went to kurns and tanked some to raise skills from 10-17, however I had my shaman healing/buffing etc.
<br />

<br />
Then I came here and learned of AoE kiting.  I was in Loio near the ruins and started pulling all the mobs there and AE kiting I got to 22 with 6 deaths in hours.  The tigers/tigresses run faster than the rest but more exp, undead are great as well because they dont run like iksars, goblinss and sarnaks.
<br />

<br />
Kiting used: AoE kiting
<br />
Where to kite: North of the ruins
<br />
What to kite:  Ideal, all tigers or tigresses or undead, but anything that roams there works
<br />

<br />
Then I started pulling all the goblins, undead, and recruits from the fort to the undead house along the bottem half of the map and AE kited them just in front of the sarnak fort(lots of flat open area for this and ideal) Leveled to 24 and the exp started to dwindle.  
<br />

<br />
Kiting used: AoE Kiting
<br />
Where to kite: Just south of the entrance to the sarnak fort
<br />
What to kite: Goblnis from the building to the south, warlord, all the sarnak recruits you can pull without a caster from the fort.
<br />

<br />

<br />
By reading the guides I went to Iceclad, got my bind from the soulbinder at the doc and pulled all the snow cougars from the gnome island.  I started out using brass+ DDD but found out i got LOTS of resists. switched to  stringed and did CoD for almost 100% lands and just twisted DDD in for extra dmg.
<br />

<br />
( I found that string + CoD  and DDD is very close in overall dmg to brass+DDD and CoD)  After I got 25 the resists on DDD went down I did just this island till about 30 and thought wait there are 2 islands here, so I pulled all of them to the flat space just north east from ToFS all of them and AEed it. 
<br />

<br />
If you can manage not to die your EXP bar will give you a level per kite- period I did this till 33.  
<br />

<br />
Kiting used: AoE
<br />
Where to kite: Gnome island at first, north of their camp is flat ground perfect for kiting.
<br />
What to kite: all snow cougars (watch out for midnight)
<br />

<br />

<br />
After this I decided to try to Spectres in Oasis, easy enough, agro one, pull them all, and I started swarm kiting with invis song.  
<br />

<br />
Kiting used: Swarm Kiting
<br />
Where to kite: Directly south of the spectre island flat ground, no adds save the random casting dry bones(hehe charm and send him to his death)
<br />
What to Kite: all the spectres
<br />

<br />
I lost sooo many pets I went on a spree of killing in loio again but this time not for exp, for the invis ring.  Never saw it in 6 days 100+ couriers dead. So I spent the cash and bought it for 50k. WORTH IT if you can afford it.
<br />

<br />
With my new shiny item in hand I went to Great Divide and pulled wolves and giants and swarmkited till 37.  Best place just west  of the Nexus Spire.  Oh and if you dont wanna kill the last mob charm it and send it at the nexus scion, just dont go near her afterwards( I would do this when I needed to log and the mob wasnt almost dead)
<br />

<br />
Kiting used: Swarm Kiting
<br />
Where to kite: Flat ground due west of the nexus spire.
<br />
What to kite: Dire wolves, frost giant recruits (rarely a berzerker)
<br />

<br />
Next I went to EW and went to the northern area and pulled all the walrus's and ulthorks(nice cash here to be made) got 38 quickly but getting to 39 was tough, took longer cause the wulrus's and ulthork hunters started giving less than 1%/kill, warriors were good.
<br />

<br />
The rhinos here are higher level, but have  TON of hp but they also have really nice DPS to knock the pet down.  When the rhino is low, chant him down, but he will run away at low health can be a pain to land chants while a swarm is still following ya.
<br />

<br />
Kiting used: Swarm Kiting
<br />
Where to kite: Nickname &quot;Sugar bowl&quot; north part of the zone, just west of the buildings there is a flat ground with a spot without trees. NE from the trigger mob for 8th ring event.
<br />
What to kite: Ulthork Warriors, Ulthork hunters, walrus's maybe rhinos
<br />

<br />
Side note on swarmkiting.  Lots of times you will get some of the mobs following you while some or just 1 mob attacks your pet, but when your pet gets low on health the swarm will leave you to finish the pet so you have to pay attention to its health, its better to break charm at 20% and chant it down than to to get greedy and lose the pet(I know this REALLY well)though I push it to the limit with instant invis ring now...
<br />

<br />
This is where I am right now 39 bard and I am about to go looking for a new place to try my new charm.  Some guides say to stick with EW doing this but imo the exp just isnt fast enough for my liking. I will update this to let ya know how/what and where to kite.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps someone.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
